</taxonomicName>
. A. Fertile branch. B. Trichomes on the petiole. C. Leaf base, abaxial surface. D. Shot and longstalked trichomes on the abaxial leaf surface. E. Hypanthium and calyx, abaxial surface. F. Stamen, lateral view. G. Ovary and style. [A, C, D, E, G: 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9249772BFF04F9F2FEE2BA7C" box="[250,371,1570,1591]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">Jardim 1823</emphasis>
; B: 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9249772BFE63F9F2FE6CBA7C" box="[413,509,1570,1591]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">Bacci 191</emphasis>
].
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C31365079249772BFF43F9B6FBF9BA83" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BB6368C9249772BFF43F9B6FBF9BA83" blockId="25.[136,1452,1638,2061]" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9249772BFF43F9B6FE29BACB" bold="true" box="[189,440,1638,1664]" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">Conservation Status:</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9249772BFE46F9B7FE40BACB" box="[440,465,1639,1664]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">—</emphasis>
The species has been found only inside a private property. 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F9249772BFBA7F9B6FACEBACB" box="[1113,1375,1638,1664]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="riocontensis">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9249772BFBA7F9B6FACEBACB" box="[1113,1375,1638,1664]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">Bertolonia riocontensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an AOO of 0 km², and should be classified as “Critically Endangered” (CR), following 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D9249772BFBC4F95AFB41BAEF" author="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee &amp; Cambridge, UK" box="[1082,1232,1674,1700]" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" refId="ref19879" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2017) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 13 (March 2017). Prepared by the IUCN species survival commission. IUCN Council, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK, 108 pp. Available from: http: // cmsdocs. s 3. amazonaws. com / RedList Guidelines. pdf (Accessed 9 February 2019)" type="book" year="2017">IUCN (2017)</bibRefCitation>
categories. Since it occurs only in one locality, it is not possible to estimate its Extent of Occurrence (EOO).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C313650792497728FF43F902FAA2BD27" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="179" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB6368C92497728FF43F902FAA2BD27" blockId="25.[136,1452,1638,2061]" lastBlockId="26.[136,1452,158,365]" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="179" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9249772BFF43F902FE98BAA7" bold="true" box="[189,265,1746,1772]" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F9249772BFED8F902FDBCBAA7" box="[294,557,1746,1772]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="riocontensis">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9249772BFED8F902FDBCBAA7" box="[294,557,1746,1772]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">Bertolonia riocontensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingRegion id="49CDF86E9249772BFD32F902FC81BAA7" box="[716,784,1746,1772]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, occurring in lowland rainforests, usually on rocky outcrops surrounded by forests on swampy areas (
<figureCitation id="13322A099249772BFDA0F926FD51BB5B" box="[606,704,1782,1808]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="19.[136,229,1730,1752]" captionTargetBox="[346,1239,435,1693]" captionTargetId="figure-140@19.[340,1247,425,1706]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 13. Distributions of species of Bertolonia in Bahia.A.Bertolonia linearifolia. B. Bertolonia maculata. C. Bertolonia marmorata. D. Bertolonia reginatoi. E. Bertolonia riocontensis. F. Bertolonia violacea. G. Bertolonia vitoriana." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597718" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597718/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">Fig. 13e</figureCitation>
). It was collected with flowers in August, and fruits in August to September. It is recognized by the branches, petioles, leaf blades, hypanthium and sepals glandulose-punctate and also glandulose-villose (trichomes 
<quantity id="4CF19B699249772BFDEDF8EEFD0ABB12" box="[531,667,1854,1881]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" unit="mm" value="2.2" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="0.9">0.9–3.5 mm</quantity>
long), thick stems (
<quantity id="4CF19B699249772BFC80F8EEFC7DBB12" box="[894,1004,1854,1881]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" unit="mm" value="8.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="5.0">5–12 mm</quantity>
wide), membranaceous and light green leaf blades with a markedly cordate base, and denticulate, densely ciliate margins. Furthermore, it has petals with an apiculate apex and stamens dehiscing through an extrorse pore. 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F9249772BFCA6F856FBF1BBEB" box="[856,1120,1926,1952]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="riocontensis">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9249772BFCA6F856FBF1BBEB" box="[856,1120,1926,1952]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">Bertolonia riocontensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F9249772BFB0AF857FAEABBEB" authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" box="[1268,1403,1926,1952]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9249772BFB0AF857FAEABBEB" box="[1268,1403,1926,1952]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">B. maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F9249772BFF76F87BFEB8BB8F" authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1851" baseAuthorityName="Naudin" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[136,297,1963,1988]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9249772BFF76F87BFEB8BB8F" box="[136,297,1963,1988]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">B. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. They all have branches, petioles, leaf blades, hypanthium and sepals glandulose-punctate and also glandulose-villose or glandulose-pilose (trichomes 
<quantity id="4CF19B699249772BFD31F81EFCD2BBA2" box="[719,835,1998,2025]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.45" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" unit="mm" value="2.45" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="0.9">0.9–4 mm</quantity>
long), ovate or widely ovate leaf blades with cordate bases, hypanthia with similar sizes (2.3–2.7 × 
<quantity id="4CF19B699249772BFD6DF822FC97B446" box="[659,774,2034,2061]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.85" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.7" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" unit="mm" value="3.85" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.7">3.7–4 mm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F9249772BFCD4F823FC42B447" box="[810,979,2035,2060]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="riocontensis">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9249772BFCD4F823FC42B447" box="[810,979,2035,2060]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">B. riocontensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 2.4–3.1 × 
<quantity id="4CF19B699249772BFBABF822FB59B446" box="[1109,1224,2034,2061]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.35" metricValueMax="3.7" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" unit="mm" value="3.35" valueMax="3.7" valueMin="3.0">3–3.7 mm</quantity>
in 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9249772BFB12F823FAEAB447" box="[1260,1403,2034,2060]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F9249772BFB12F823FAE6B447" authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" box="[1260,1399,2034,2060]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculata">B. maculata</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 1.8–2.9 × 
<quantity id="4CF19B69924A7728FF09FF4EFEF6BCF3" box="[247,359,158,185]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.207" metricValueMax="6.35" metricValueMin="4.064" pageId="26" pageNumber="179" unit="in" value="2.05" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="1.6">1.6–2.5 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F924A7728FE92FF4FFD99BCF3" authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1851" baseAuthorityName="Naudin" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[364,520,159,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="26" pageNumber="179" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E924A7728FE92FF4FFD99BCF3" box="[364,520,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="179">B. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and petals with an apiculate apex. 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F924A7728FC71FF4EFB07BCF3" box="[911,1174,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="26" pageNumber="179" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="riocontensis">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E924A7728FC71FF4EFB07BCF3" box="[911,1174,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="179">Bertolonia riocontensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F924A7728FADBFF4FFA3ABCF3" authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" box="[1317,1451,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="26" pageNumber="179" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E924A7728FADBFF4FFA3ABCF3" box="[1317,1451,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="179">B. maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the leaf blades with denticulate and densely ciliate margins (
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E924A7728FCA4FF13FCE0BC97" box="[858,881,195,220]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="179">vs</emphasis>
. entire and moderately ciliate in 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F924A7728FB17FF13FAE0BC97" authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" box="[1257,1393,194,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="26" pageNumber="179" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E924A7728FB17FF13FAE0BC97" box="[1257,1393,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="179">B. maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and anthers dehiscing through an extrorse pore with non-thickened margins (
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E924A7728FC4FFF37FC59BD4B" box="[945,968,231,256]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="179">vs</emphasis>
. anthers dehiscing through an introrse pore with thickened margins). 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F924A7728FE5DFEDAFD3BBD6F" box="[419,682,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="26" pageNumber="179" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="riocontensis">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E924A7728FE5DFEDAFD3BBD6F" box="[419,682,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="179">Bertolonia riocontensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F924A7728FCC5FEDBFC46BD6F" authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1851" baseAuthorityName="Naudin" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[827,983,267,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="26" pageNumber="179" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E924A7728FCC5FEDBFC46BD6F" box="[827,983,267,292]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="179">B. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the leaf blades with an acuminate apex (
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E924A7728FF6FFEFFFF39BD03" box="[145,168,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="179">vs</emphasis>
. rounded or obtuse in 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F924A7728FE4FFEFFFDC0BD03" authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1851" baseAuthorityName="Naudin" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[433,593,303,328]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="26" pageNumber="179" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E924A7728FE4FFEFFFDC0BD03" box="[433,593,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="179">B. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and stamens dehiscing through an extrorse and rounded pore (
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E924A7728FACDFEFFFADBBD03" box="[1331,1354,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="179">vs</emphasis>
. anthers dehiscing through an introrse and triangular pore). For more details see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D924A7728FC52FE82FB35BD27" author="Bisewski, G. C. A. &amp; Bacci, L. &amp; Amorim, A. M. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R." box="[940,1188,338,364]" pageId="26" pageNumber="179" pagination="563 - 574" refId="ref18940" refString="Bisewski, G. C. A., Bacci, L. F, Amorim, A. M. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R. (2020) Novelties in Bertolonia (Melastomataceae) from northeastern Brazil. Brazilian Journal of Botany 43 (3): 563 - 574. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 40415 - 020 - 00630 - 7" type="journal article" year="2020">
Bisewski 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E924A7728FBE4FE83FBC3BD27" box="[1050,1106,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="179">et al.</emphasis>
(2020)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<tableCitation id="C68B0337924A7728FB27FE82FABCBD27" box="[1241,1325,338,364]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="6.[136,224,623,649]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="TABLE 1. Selected morphological characters scored for species in Bertolonia that occur in the state of Bahia, Brazil. “GP”= Glandulose-punctate; “GV”= Glandulose-villose." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF76660492567734FF76FDBFF843BEC2" pageId="26" pageNumber="179" tableUuid="DF76660492567734FF76FDBFF843BEC2">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
